We can keep, again, we can keep all the data inside of Databricks to perform the aggregation of this and then finally collect the resulting aggregation into our R session

00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:14.000
and then work with other tools within R like ggplot, for example, to create some sort of a visualization of whatever it is that we're investigating.

