00:47:01.000 --> 00:47:07.000
When Posit Connect tries to publish whatever it is that I submitted, in this case, that would be this Cordo document.

00:47:07.000 --> 00:47:13.000
It will first recreate the environment it needs to run that content and it will do this in isolation.

00:47:13.000 --> 00:47:17.000
So I do not have to worry about managing a complex network of dependencies on Connect.

00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:21.000
Instead, every piece of content has its own collection of dependencies.

00:47:21.000 --> 00:47:24.000
There's a shared cache, so I'm not duplicating work.

00:47:24.000 --> 00:47:28.000
But it means that everything can operate in isolation without interference with other content.

00:47:28.000 --> 00:47:35.000
So if this dashboard uses some version of PySpark that another dashboard uses a different version of PySpark,

00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:41.000
there's not going to be a conflict when it comes to publishing and sharing on Posit Connect.

00:47:41.000 --> 00:47:50.000
The other advantage of using this RS Connect package is that it allows me to pass local environment variables in a very secure way to Posit Connect.

